title: [Social Science] Study finds states with Republican governors had worse COVID-19 outcomes

[Epidemiology] A report of the impact of population-wide rapid antigen testing on SARS-CoV-2 prevalence in Slovakia found that SARS-CoV-2 prevalence decreased by 58% (estimated 70% decrease adjusting for epidemic growth) in one week in the 45 counties subject to two rounds of mass testing
